  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Spring Sentiments
  author: Jeong Mong-ju
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The spring rain falls so fine
    no drops can be heard—
    yet in the night's stillness
    a whisper of sound emerges.

    Snow melts into the southern stream,
    swelling its banks.
    How many grass shoots
    have already broken through the earth?
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The poem captures the subtle awakening of spring, where transformation occurs so gradually it escapes notice until suddenly, all at once, spring has arrived.
